description: Lazerman has scattered the mob of zombies, and the city has seemingly been saved from a legion of the undead...but has the crisis really been averted, or is a more sinister plan unfolding? The night of the Necrolord continues!

description: The Borderhounds are back in this sensational new series! Brimstone & his team of Borderhounds must go up against the Multiverse's elite in the ultimate showdown! A prized "soul" has been mysteriously plucked from the Nexus and deposited in the Wasteland. Now all the major corporations of the Multiverse have sent in their best retrieval units to claim it!
name: Contest

deck: Necrocide is the first special edition released under the 'Brimstone and The Borderhounds' series.  Brimstone makes his way to the Necroverse for an all new and interesting take on the zombie genre.
name: Necrocide

description:
Line Officer

He had fought with the best of them -- up and down the rugged peninsula -- and he had seen his officers come and go! But to a fighting man, his C.O. had to be just one thing --- he had to know the score -- he had to think of his men first -- in short, he had to be a ... Line Officer

The Gambler! (Text Only Story)

The Big Birds

The fighter pilot always felt sorry for his brother pilot who flew the heavy bombers! And laughed at his ability -- there was nothing to fly the heavies -- it wasn't even piloting -- that was being a taxi cab driver -- a meter reader! It was only when you were alone in the sky in your tiny pursuit ship that you became a pilot!

Buddha Smiled

The American patrol edged toward the temple that lay partially hidden -- and a pair of unseeing eyes watched them -- the huge idol -- the stone statue watched -- and --- Buddha Smiled

Patrol! (Text Only Story)

Coward

The men didn't like the young officer.... hated hit guts -- for --- the Captain was a... Coward

description: The magic has returned! But, this time‚Ä¶the light has grown dark. As the war of ages between the Sethoru and the Rahtumi rages on to its climactic finish, Malikai must confront a deeply startling revelation - the malevolent chaos creatures that have been tormenting the world--are actually part of his own soul! How can the Bearer of the Light possibly defeat an evil that grows within himself? And what means can he possibly turn to in order to contain a darkness that feeds on the very light of the living? Don't miss out on the shocking conclusion to the epic third volume of SOULFIRE! New adversaries, exotic locations, and a fresh cast of exciting characters, including some from the Soulfire Universe's long forgotten past, reign supreme in this finale to the epic third SOULFIRE volume!
name: Extinguished

description: Green Hornet battles Green Hornet, to the death. The people of Century City are convinced that Britt Reid, as Green Hornet, murdered the city's Mayor. The only way for Britt to clear his name is to track down the real killer. When Green Hornet comes face to face with his doppelganger, it may just turn out to be the last fight of his life. If Britt Reid can't defeat the costumed imposter that framed him, a hero's legacy will be destroyed forever, and Century City will fall into the hands of the evil mastermind who orchestrated the whole setup. The Outcast storyline rolls on toward its thunderous conclusion.
name: Outcast, Part Four of Six

description: Creator Lora Innes writes and illustrates the tale of 17-year-old Beatrice 'Bea' Whaley, a student who begins having vivid dreams about a brave and handsome soldier that fought during the Revolutionary War. Prone to keeping her head in the clouds, Bea welcomes her nightly adventures in 1776. But it is not long before Beatrice questions whether her dreams are simply dreams or something more.
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: The Dreamer: The Battle of Brooklyn

name: Mickey Mouse and the Stagecoach Bandits

description: For the first time in comics Nancy Drew and The Hardy Boys team up! There's trouble in River Heights - Nancy Drew's longtime boyfriend Ned Nickerson has run off into the waiting arms of Dierdre Shannon. But that's not the worst of it. Someone has been secretly plotting against Nancy for some time. It's more trouble than Nancy Drew can handle on her own, which is why she needs the Hardy Boys' help. Just one problem: Joe and Frank no longer want to work together!
name: Together With the Hardy Boys

description:
No intergalactic terrorist threats, no plots to overthrow the United Galactica, no 7:00 a.m. training runs -- it's just a relaxing vacation for Kei and Yuri, also known as the Lovely Angels, also known as the Dirty Pair. But their poolside bash goes bust when an old friend -- Shasti -- turns up at the same vacation spot! Shasti was their partner, a genetically-engineered superagent for the 3WA, until she betrayed the Pair. And now it's payback time!

Contents

  • Things Past
  • Dangerous Acquaintances
  • Unquiet Zone
  • One Of My Turns
  • Ground Zero

volume.name: The Dirty Pair Book Two: Dangerous Acquaintances Collection

name: Fantomet

description: THE MORRIGAN WARS begin anew! For the first time in color, it's Part One of the classic crossover between the LEAGUE OF CHAMPIONS and the SOUTHERN KNIGHTS. This is a book-length, 27-page adventure, with story by Henry Vogel and Dennis Mallonee, artwork by Howard Simpson, Mark Propst, and George Perez!

THE MORRIGAN WARS begin anew! For the first time in color, it's Part Two of the classic crossover between the LEAGUE OF CHAMPIONS and the SOUTHERN KNIGHTS. This is a book-length, 26-page adventure, with story by Henry Vogel and Dennis Mallonee, artwork by Lou Manna and Mark Propst. Cover by George Perez!

THE MORRIGAN WARS continue! For the first time in color, it's Part Four of the classic crossover between the LEAGUE OF CHAMPIONS and the SOUTHERN KNIGHTS. This is a book-length, 28-page adventure, with story by Henry Vogel and Dennis Mallonee, artwork by Scott Clark and Mark Propst.

THE MORRIGAN WARS conclude! And the CHAMPIONS hit a milestone in this super-sized 50th issue! For the first time in color, enjoy the thrilling 41-page conclusion to the classic crossover between the LEAGUE OF CHAMPIONS and the SOUTHERN KNIGHTS. "The Morrigan Wars" is by writers Henry Vogel and Dennis Mallonee, featuring artwork by Mark Propst! Also in this issue, taken directly from the Flare Sunday newspaper comic strip from Creators Syndicate, it's the first-ever actual fight between FLARE and the ever-naughty BLACK ENCHANTRESS, by Dennis Mallonee and Sean Harrington. Cover by Mark Propst.

In this 51st issue of Champions, enjoy an all-new adventure starring Flare's electric little sister SPARKPLUG! When ace reporter Jimmy Dooley sees Sparks flying away from Olga Gottmann's apartment, he thinks he's finally about to prove that Olga and Sparkplug are one and the same! Problem is, there's another Jimmy in the mix! And the SENSATIONAL G-GIRL's kid brother Jimmy Jensen is determined to do whatever it takes to safeguard Olga's secret! "Two Jimmys Too Many" is brought to you by writer Steve Perrin and artist James Webb. Also in this issue, the savage TIGRESS is back, facing down the sinister SERPENT is the classic adventure, "A Tryst in Time," by Dennis Mallonee, Paul Abrams, and Craig Stormon.

Everyone's favorite little liar takes center stage in this 52nd issue of Champions when she finds herself accidentally teaming up with none other than the fabulous FLYING FOX! It's a Jim Valentino tour de force in the classic adventure, "The Icon and the Icicle."

Also in this issue, the savage TIGRESS is back, facing down the sinister SERPENT in the classic adventure, "Harpyra," by Dennis Mallonee, Paul Abrams, and Craig Stormon.

It's a double-dose of artist ROB JONES in this 53rd issue of Champions, with two all-new adventures starring SPARKPLUG and ICICLE!

First, when word reaches SPARKPLUG that clues to the whereabouts of her long-missing brother TOMAS may have been found in Germany, it's time to head for Europe. Trouble is, it's a trap! "Sparks on a Plane" is by Dennis Mallonee, with full artwork and colors by Rob Jones.

And when an old adversary returns to challenge ICICLE, get ready for a "Throwdown with Power Pulse," with story by Dennis Mallonee, layouts by Lou Manna, finished artwork and colors by Rob Jones.

Two stories end (Flesh and Anderson) and two begin (Grey Area and Durham Red), plus a new Day of Chaos story in Judge Dredd.

A raft of cameo appearances this prog, including Earl Reagan and Claw Carver (Flesh), Vienna (Judge Dredd) and Johnny Alpha and Wulf Sternhammer (featuring their first meeting with Durham Red).

Cover: Carlos Ezquerra (Durham Red)

  • Judge Dredd - Day of Chaos - Tea for Two (John Wagner - Edmund Bagwell)
  • Flesh - Midnight Cowboys (part 12 - final part) (Pat Mills - James McKay)
  • Durham Red - The 'Nobody Wants This Job' Job (part 1) (Alan Grant - Carlos Ezquerra)
  • Grey Area - One of Our Own (part 1) (Dan Abnett - Lee Carter)
  • Cadet Anderson - Algol (part 6 - final part) (Alan Grant - Steve Yeowell)
name: Prog 1785

description: Get ready for the ready for the return of Heroic Publishing's mistress of the occult with the classic book-length adventure, "Bats," from the pages of LADY ARCANE #1, by writers Dennis Mallonee and Colin Wales, with artwork by Duval Stowers. Cover by Duval Stowers amd Mark Beachum.

For the first time in color, our shining goddess of the light stars in the classic adventure, "From L.A. with Love," by Dennis Mallonee, Shawn Atkinson, and Jeff Brennan. When Flare lets slip the possibility that she might leave Los Angeles, the city fathers begin an all-out effort to convince her to stay in town. But the question is, who's really behind it? Then, in "Togas or Jeans? Just Say Nyx," by Dennis Mallonee and Flare's newest artist, Alex Amezcua, find out how Flare finally managed to persuade her arch-rival NYX, goddess of the night, that Sergio Klein jeans are way cool. All this, plus an all-new bonus adventure of DOLF by Dennis Mallonee and Duval Stowers.
name: From L.A. With Love; Dolf and the Pretty Pony; Sergio Klein Jeans: A Gift of the Gods

description: It's our shining goddess of the light's "Farewell to the City of Angels." Classic Flare artist MARK PROPST returns for an all-new blast from the past that tells the never-before-told story of how and why our glittering heroine decided that being a CHAMPION was far more important to her than pursuing an acting career. And it features guest appearances by LADY ARCANE, the invincible THUGMASTER, and the savage original TIGRESS! Also in this issue, enjoy the classic adventure, "Joyride," by Dennis Mallonee, Kevin Tuma, and Craig Stormon.

Barbara Thorson, a girl battling monsters both real and imagined, kicks butt, takes names, and faces her greatest fear in the bittersweet coming-of-age story called 'Best Indy Book of 2008' by IGN. AICN says '. . . a great mini full of eccentricity, humor and humanity that I not only highly recommend, but hope to see get some well-deserved attention come Eisner time.' This is a LIMITED EDITION OVERSIZED PRINTING and will not be printed again.
name: TPB

A declaration of war is sent to the Soul Society from the mysterious Vandenreich, an army of quincies controlled by an ancient enemy of Captain Yamamoto. Meanwhile, Ichigo and his friends ventures once more to Hueco Mundo already under the grip of the new enemy.

Caitlin, upset with the loss of her parents and unhappy with life in the country is full of a rebellious temper that leads to trouble!

After being sent to from her home in Seattle to live with her great aunt in the west of Ireland, orphaned teenager Caitlin MacNamara stumbles into a world of myth, magic and danger!
